    "text": "Fine-tuning for helpfulness increases susceptibility to training data extraction attacks by amplifying output variance, which creates a measurable side-channel: the logit variance across diverse prompts serves as a predictor of success for membership inference, with helpfulness-tuned models leaking at least 20% more private sequences than accuracy-tuned models under identical gradient attack protocols.",
