    "text": "Contamination artifacts in an agent's persistent context (multi-turn chat histories) produce latent encodings that, when decoded by a probing classifier, can reconstruct high-entropy training text snippets with accuracy exceeding 40%, analogous to the privacy backdoor in federated fine-tuning but exploiting real-time session contamination rather than model parameter leakage.",
    "topic": "contamination-driven-extraction"
  }
